'''Tim Molloy''' is a [[New Zealand]] [[illustrator]] and comic artist, living and working in [[Melbourne]].<ref>http://hatch.jackywinter.com/artists/tim-molloy</ref>  Molloy's work has appeared in [[Tango (comics)|Tango]],<ref>http://www.cardigancomics.com/index.php/tango/tango7-love-sedition.html</ref> ''Torpedo''<ref>http://www.readings.com.au/product/9780980403961/torpedo-issue-6</ref> and ''Desktop Magazine''.<ref>http://blog.jackywinter.com/category/artists/timmolloy/</ref> In 2007 he published a collection of his comic art as ''Under the Bed''.<ref>http://www.cannedgeek.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=87</ref> Since 2006 he has collaborated with writer Adam Lachlan to produce ''Life on Earth'' cartoons.<ref>http://www.lifeonearthcartoons.com/index.htm</ref> Recently he has published two [[graphic novel]]s, ''It Shines and Shakes and Laughs'' and ''Mr Unpronounceable Adventures'' through Australian publisher, [[Milk Shadow Books]].

As a promotion for the web series Zombies On Ramsay Street, Molloy was employed to zombify a number of press social media profiles. He gave the same treatment to [[MyM|MyM magazine's]] official mascot Mya Tenshi, in Issue 31.

